reviews.review: A fantastic ending to the Skywalker Saga and a great sendoff to our Space Mom.
Best of the last 3.  Great story and ending to a 41 year journey!  Loved it!

Far better than The Last Jedi, but still incoherent Story. Just a lot of bland characters in clued together 'cool scenes'. The whole new trilogy has been a horrifying mess which only made money on the back of the IP that it canabalised,

First, this is a fantastic movie and I enjoyed it very much.
Second, this was a great way to end the Skywalker saga. I am excited to see what Disney/Lucasfilm does next.
Third, now I just need to decide when I want to go see it again and then count the days until it releases on digital because I will definitely be buying it then too.

Seeing the original in 1977 created a true relationship with the series so yes I am a true fan boy. That being said I was slightly disappointed in many of the directions the movies decided to go after Return of the Jedi. Midichlorians, Greedo shooting first, bad green screen prequels, Jar Jar, kiddie level sequences, life resurrecting force powers, etc. I am glad that Snopes was explained as well as Leia's Jedi training. It was a fan movie and unless you discovered the series as a kid it will work with you on a different level. Of course it has it flaws but not so much as the prequels and TLJ. I enjoyed it very much.

Of all the movies I've watched this year, this was easily the worst one. The first time I watched it, I couldn't believe what I was seeing, because if honestly felt like fanfiction written by a 13 year old. This movie completely ignores the previous two and tries to fit the story of a whole trilogy in one movie. It feels rushed and lazy, and they tried to hide that behind nostalgia and pretty visual effects. The second time I watched it (I only went because my friends wanted me to go with them) I was bored out of my mind and all I wanted was to leave. This movie also completely undermines the original trilogy, which is absurd. So, save your money and go watch something else.
